The United States has condemned the Taliban's attack on a restaurant in Kabul, Afghanistan, which resulted in the death of 21 civilians and injuries to others. The attack targeted innocent civilians, including Americans who were working to support the Afghan people's education and economic development. The United States sends condolences to the victims and their families and calls for a swift recovery for the injured. The Afghan security services responded quickly and effectively to the attack. The United States urges the Taliban to lay down their arms and engage in peace talks to bring an end to the conflict in a peaceful manner.